From 44135f92a7c9350e71419eb55a4d0ac4b7cf2d31 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 14:52:44 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 123/174] mm/util: randomize_stack_top aligns to MMUPAGE, not
 PAGE

Same overshoot pattern as commit e45ede859836 (fs/exec: align stack_top
to MMUPAGE granularity). randomize_stack_top() returned
PAGE_ALIGN(stack_top) [- random_variable]. Under page clustering with
PAGE_SIZE > MMUPAGE_SIZE, when the input stack_top is MMUPAGE-aligned
but not PAGE-aligned (s390x STACK_TOP = VDSO_LIMIT - vdso_size() -
PAGE_SIZE ends in 0xc000), PAGE_ALIGN rounds up past STACK_TOP_MAX,
and the small random_variable (~0..a few MB) cannot bring the result
back below the temporary-stack VMA's vm_end.

binfmt_elf is the dominant caller (binfmt_elf.c:1031), so the bad
return value lands directly in setup_arg_pages, where stack_shift =
vma->vm_end - stack_top wraps negative. relocate_vma_down then
computes new_start = old_start - shift wrapping to just above
old_start; vma_expand stores a new tree entry covering only the new
range, leaving the old tree entry's left portion intact -> two tree
slots referencing the same VMA -> validate_mm's i > mm->map_count
check trips BUG_ON during execve.

Reproduced on s390x PGCL=4 as 1/74 verify-loop runs after the exec.c
fix; root cause traced to randomize_stack_top by the matching VMA
range pattern (vm_start advanced into the original temp-stack range by
a small multiple of MMUPAGE_SIZE).

Signed-off-by: Nadia Yvette Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@gmail.com>
---
 mm/util.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/util.c b/mm/util.c
index dcd27bacb6b5..0cd11e262d32 100644
--- a/mm/util.c
+++ b/mm/util.c
@@ -348,9 +348,9 @@ unsigned long randomize_stack_top(unsigned long stack_top)
 		random_variable <<= PAGE_SHIFT;
 	}
 #ifdef CONFIG_STACK_GROWSUP
-	return PAGE_ALIGN(stack_top) + random_variable;
+	return MMUPAGE_ALIGN(stack_top) + random_variable;
 #else
-	return PAGE_ALIGN(stack_top) - random_variable;
+	return MMUPAGE_ALIGN(stack_top) - random_variable;
 #endif
 }
 
